2: Kafka Cluster and Broker
   Kafka Cluster multiple Brokers ka collection hota hai. Broker basically ek Kafka Server hota hai jo messages ko store aur serve karne ka kaam karta hai.

3: Producer, Consumer aur Topic 
   Producer messages ko Topic me publish karta hai. 
   Consumer Topic ko subscribe karta hai aur usme se messages read karta hai.
   Topic ek logical category hoti hai jisme related messages group kiye jaate hain.
   
   Example:
   
   Orders
   Payments
   Notifications

4: Topic aur Partitions 
   Topic Partition/s me divided hota hai.
   Example:

   Suppose 'Orders' Topic has 3 partitions.

   Partition-0
   Partition-1
   Partition-2

   Ye Partitions:
   Ek hi Broker par store ho sakte hai Ya multiple Brokers me distribute ho sakte hain

   Example:

   Broker-1
   Partition-0

   Broker-2
   Partition-1

   Broker-3
   Partition-2

   Ye sabse common scenario hai.

   Topic multiple Partitions me divided hota hai,and ye Partitions kisi 1 broker mai stored ho sakte hai ya phir multiple Multiple Brokers ke across stored ho sakte hai

   Agar cluster me sirf ek hi Broker ho ya Kafka ne waise assign kiya ho, to saare Partitions ek hi Broker par bhi store ho sakte hain.

   Example:

   Broker-1

   Partition-0
   Partition-1
   Partition-2

   Ye bhi possible hai.

   Lekin generally Partitions multiple Brokers me distributed rehte hain.


5: Offset:
   Har Partition ke andar har message ko ek unique Offset milta hai. Offset ek index ki tarah kaam karta hai jo message ki position batata hai.

   Maan lo Producer ne messages A, B, C, D aur E isi sequence me publish kiye hain.

   Suppose:
   Topic : "my-topic"
   It has only 1 partition

   Partition-0

   Offset 0 -> A
   Offset 1 -> B
   Offset 2 -> C
   Offset 3 -> D
   Offset 4 -> E

   Kyuki Topic me sirf ek hi Partition hai, isliye saare messages sequentially isi Partition me store honge.

   Consumer messages read karta hai partition se aur apna Offset commit karta rehta hai.

   Agar Consumer ne "C" successfully process kar liya aur Offset commit kar diya, to generally next read:

   Offset 3 -> D

   se start hogi.

   Kafka committed Offset ko store karke rakhta hai.

   Agar Consumer restart ho jaye, to Kafka last committed Offset check karta hai.

  Example:

  Last Committed Offset = 3

  To Consumer dubara start hote hi:

   Offset 3 -> D

  se reading continue karega.

  Consumer chahe to committed Offset ignore karke beginning se bhi read kar sakta hai.

  Example:

  "Mujhe saare messages dobara process karne hain."

  To Consumer:

  Offset 0 -> A

  se reading start kar sakta hai.


