7: Do we duplicate partions of a topic across multiple partitions ?

Production mai Kafka me almost hamesha partitions ki copies (replicas) multiple brokers par rakhi jaati hain.

Ye Kafka ka Replication concept hai.

Without Replication

Maan lo:

'Orders' Topic is having 3 partitions:

Partition-0 -> Broker-1
Partition-1 -> Broker-2
Partition-2 -> Broker-3

Diagram:

+-------------------+
| Broker-1          |
| Partition-0       |
+-------------------+

+-------------------+
| Broker-2          |
| Partition-1       |
+-------------------+

+-------------------+
| Broker-3          |
| Partition-2       |
+-------------------+

Ab agar:

Broker-1 crash ho gaya

To:

Partition-0 ka sara data gaya

Aur us partition ka data temporarily unavailable / /permanently lost ho jayega.

Case 1: Broker crash hua, lekin disk safe hai
To jab broker wapas aayega: Partition-0 ka data wapas mil jayega.

Case 2: Broker permanently gaya

Suppose:

Disk crash
Server destroy ho gaya
Data corrupt ho gaya
Cloud VM delete ho gayi

To: Partition-0 ka data permanently lost.

Bahut dangerous.


With Replication

Suppose:

Replication Factor = 3

Matlab:

Har partition ki total 3 copies hongi.

Example:

Orders Topic

