Partition-2 (Follower)

------------------------------------------------

Broker-3

Partition-2 (Leader)
Partition-0 (Follower)

------------------------------------------------

Important Terminology

Leader Replica

Har partition ka ek leader hota hai.

Producer jo bhi message publish karta hai and wo message us partion mai agar map/store hota hai to wo uske Leader parttion mai store hoga

Baaki copies/replica  followers hoti hain.

Leader partion

   |

   +----> Follower partition

   |

   +----> Follower partition



Ye continuously leader partition se data copy karti rehti hain.

and cosmuemr hamesha jab bhi is partion se date read karna hoga to wo hamesha isi leader partion se data read karega


Imagine karo ki :


Broker-1 crash ho jata hai jisme ki  Partition-0 Leader tha

Kafka bolega:

Koi tension nahi.

Follower ko promote kar do.

Broker-3

Partition-0

Follower ---> Leader

ab going forward producer aur consumer naye leader se baat karenge. i.e producer ka agar koi message map hot ahai partion-0 mai to broker-3 ka partion-0 mai stroe hoga and consuemr bhi yaha se consume karega.


Kafka uses replication. Each partition can have multiple replicas distributed across different brokers. One replica acts as the leader and the remaining replicas act as followers for fault tolerance and high availability.

Kya Ek Partition Ki Multiple Copies Same Broker Me Ho Sakti Hain?
NO

Kafka allow nahi karta.

Galat:

